02:02.600 --> 02:03.589
Whoo!

02:18.000 --> 02:18.989
(SHRILL WHISTLE)

02:19.080 --> 02:21.275
(MUSIC PLAYING)

02:21.360 --> 02:22.349
Whoo!

02:29.400 --> 02:30.389
WOMAN: Whoa!

02:43.120 --> 02:45.156
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

02:45.360 --> 02:46.349
Yeah!

02:50.200 --> 02:51.189
Whoo!

02:59.400 --> 03:00.628
Yay!
Oh!

03:00.720 --> 03:01.709
(CHEERING)

03:04.560 --> 03:07.393
Check her out! Yeah! Yeah!

03:09.400 --> 03:10.389
Ha!

03:12.160 --> 03:13.479
(ALL CHEERING)

03:13.560 --> 03:15.312
Shake it! Yes!
(CHUCKLES)

03:15.560 --> 03:16.879
Ha! Ha!

03:19.400 --> 03:20.389
(SCOFFS)

03:21.840 --> 03:23.831
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

03:28.200 --> 03:29.189
(LAUGHING)

03:41.520 --> 03:43.033
WOMAN: Come on, shake it!

03:46.520 --> 03:47.509
Whoo!

03:53.840 --> 03:54.955
Yeah!

04:31.120 --> 04:32.109
(LAUGHS)

04:35.120 --> 04:36.109
Yeah.

04:36.200 --> 04:38.350
You and your drama, Nadine.

04:38.440 --> 04:39.998
Do you always have to
make such an entrance?

04:40.840 --> 04:43.035
I am nothing if not dramatic.

04:43.120 --> 04:44.439
(CHUCKLING)

04:44.520 --> 04:45.839
How long have
you known me for?

04:45.920 --> 04:48.514
Well, since our mothers
grew up here together,

04:48.640 --> 04:50.312
I would have to say
before we were born.

04:50.680 --> 04:51.999
Mm-hmm. And that's how
it's gonna stay.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.032
From womb to tomb, baby!

04:54.120 --> 04:55.872
I know that's right.
Got this tonight.

04:55.960 --> 04:57.313
You guys are crazy.
(NADINE LAUGHS)

04:57.840 --> 05:00.308
And you love it.
Yeah, I do. I do.

05:01.840 --> 05:04.912
You know, being around them, it makes
me miss being with someone special.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.479
And, baby, you are so on my...

05:06.560 --> 05:07.709
Okay. You...

05:07.840 --> 05:11.071
You need to not touch me. I'm not
trying to hear that. (CHUCKLES) Oh!

05:11.200 --> 05:13.668
Yo, give it up, Laser.
Whatever, man.

05:13.760 --> 05:15.034
I'm ready to go, anyway.

05:15.120 --> 05:17.759
Yeah, we should go, too.
We have class in the morning.

05:17.840 --> 05:18.875
You go ahead.

05:18.960 --> 05:20.518
I'm gonna hang out with Nadine
for a little while.

05:21.200 --> 05:22.599
Come on,
I'll see you tomorrow.

05:22.680 --> 05:24.193
Don't be too late.
I won't.

05:25.160 --> 05:26.275
Bye, ladies.
Bye.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.191
Have fun. Not too much.

05:29.200 --> 05:31.236
Yeah, he's a good one.

05:32.200 --> 05:35.636
Maybe I should come to your fancy
university and snag me a cutie, too.

05:35.720 --> 05:37.472
Been trying to tell you.

05:37.560 --> 05:38.754
Girl, I have a job.

05:39.080 --> 05:41.992
I'm just saying, you have other
talents besides teaching.

05:42.120 --> 05:45.829
You can't let all of this go to waste.
(LAUGHS)

05:45.920 --> 05:47.751
Oh, no, it won't,
'cause, um...

05:48.360 --> 05:50.715
See that guy at the bar? Yeah.

05:50.800 --> 05:54.270
Yeah, well, he's about to pay
for my drinks all night. Oh-ho!

05:54.560 --> 05:55.549
Can I get you something?

05:55.640 --> 05:56.629
I'm not drinking.

05:56.720 --> 05:58.631
You know, MeMe,
we give the people a show.

05:58.720 --> 06:00.915
The least they can do
is buy our refreshments.

06:01.440 --> 06:02.509
Have fun.

06:07.600 --> 06:08.828
It's time for a real battle.

06:09.760 --> 06:11.318
(CHUCKLES) What?
(SCOFFS)

06:14.760 --> 06:16.113
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

06:16.200 --> 06:18.430
Come on, guys.
Let's kick some ass.

06:18.920 --> 06:19.909
(CHUCKLES)

06:23.840 --> 06:25.068
Yeah!

06:25.760 --> 06:26.749
Yes!

06:37.120 --> 06:38.155
All right.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.036
(CHEERING)

06:44.360 --> 06:45.839
Who are they?

06:46.040 --> 06:47.553
I have no idea.

06:53.440 --> 06:54.759
Okay, you gotta
take this for me.

07:00.160 --> 07:01.309
Let's do this.

07:15.840 --> 07:16.955
Yeah.

07:19.800 --> 07:20.949
Yeah!

07:43.160 --> 07:44.275
Come on, please.

07:54.200 --> 07:55.315
ZUBAIR: (OVER SPEAKER)
Not tonight, guys.

07:55.400 --> 07:57.231
Security, security!
Take this out.

07:59.760 --> 08:02.718
Damn. Every time.
This ain't over.

08:03.480 --> 08:04.674
Oh, we're just
getting started.

08:07.960 --> 08:09.313
Yo! Hey, hey!

08:09.920 --> 08:11.751
Hey! What are you doing?
Stay out of it.

08:15.240 --> 08:17.435
Let's go. What are they
even fighting for?

08:18.800 --> 08:19.835
I told you!

08:20.560 --> 08:21.913
MELEA: It wasn't
that big a deal.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.673
Things just get a little crazy
between cliques there sometimes.

08:24.760 --> 08:26.113
ERIK: I knew I shouldn't
have left you alone.

08:26.880 --> 08:29.792
I wasn't alone. I was
with Nadine and my crew.

08:30.520 --> 08:32.158
Your crew?
Yeah.

08:32.799 --> 08:34.870
Just 'cause you spent
your summers growing up here,

08:34.960 --> 08:37.315
(CLEARS THROAT)
does not make you from here.

08:37.400 --> 08:38.879
And you need to relax.

08:38.960 --> 08:40.712
Nothing bad happened.

08:40.799 --> 08:42.153
In fact,
I learned some new moves

08:42.240 --> 08:43.753
from this girl that I battled.

08:44.240 --> 08:45.559
(SIGHS) She was dope.

08:46.640 --> 08:48.153
(CHUCKLES) I think I might
use some of the moves

08:48.240 --> 08:49.912
in my Romeo and Juliet thesis.

08:50.640 --> 08:51.959
You have such
a one-track mind.

08:52.040 --> 08:54.156
Is it always
about dance with you?

08:54.240 --> 08:55.514
No, occasionally,
it's about you.

08:55.600 --> 08:57.192
Occasionally?
Mm-hmm.

08:57.280 --> 08:58.269
Oh, okay.

08:58.640 --> 09:01.074
Well, you know, I'm busy.
Got a lot of stuff to do.

09:01.160 --> 09:02.195
You're so busy.

09:02.280 --> 09:03.269
(CHUCKLES)

09:03.360 --> 09:04.759
Are you too busy for this?

09:05.680 --> 09:07.318
Nope. I'm late for class.
(CHUCKLES)

09:07.440 --> 09:08.589
Okay, cool.

09:09.760 --> 09:11.990
Oh, you have some new tracks
for me later, right?

09:12.600 --> 09:13.828
Yes, Captain.

09:13.920 --> 09:15.114
Stupid. (CHUCKLES)

09:16.120 --> 09:20.671
EDUARDO: Five, six...
Five, six, seven, hit it.

09:20.760 --> 09:22.796
(MUSIC PLAYING)

09:31.920 --> 09:32.955
Yes!

09:34.400 --> 09:35.389
Yeah!

09:44.240 --> 09:45.229
Whoo!

09:50.080 --> 09:51.513
Go, go, go.

09:51.920 --> 09:53.114
Yeah!

09:54.640 --> 09:55.709
Yeah!

10:00.360 --> 10:01.349
Hey!
(CHUCKLES)

10:01.440 --> 10:03.476
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

10:04.520 --> 10:05.999
Hold on. I need to take this.

10:07.320 --> 10:08.435
Yeah?

10:10.520 --> 10:12.954
Yo, Melea, that was hot.

10:13.040 --> 10:14.951
And I'm gonna need you
to run it by me again later.

10:15.240 --> 10:17.390
Why? You jealous that
I got some moves you don't?

10:17.480 --> 10:18.993
He is.
Hey.

10:19.080 --> 10:20.149
What?
(CHUCKLES)

10:20.240 --> 10:23.152
Melea. Administrator
wants to see you.

10:26.160 --> 10:27.354
So, go.

10:29.600 --> 10:31.431
Okay, guys, let's take it
from the top.

10:31.520 --> 10:32.839
Do I have to tell you twice?

10:33.160 --> 10:34.479
Let's go.

10:35.400 --> 10:37.436
(INDISTINCT)

10:50.680 --> 10:53.319
Melea, whatever it is,
we'll figure something out.

10:53.400 --> 10:54.628
There's nothing
to figure out, Erik.

10:54.720 --> 10:56.119
I'm getting kicked
out of school,

10:56.200 --> 10:59.078
and I won't be able to
present my thesis project.

10:59.160 --> 11:02.630
It's our thesis project, and
I'm just as upset as you are.

11:03.160 --> 11:04.195
No, you're not.

11:04.760 --> 11:06.159
Come over,
and we'll talk about it.

11:06.720 --> 11:09.029
Please? I can't.
I'll call you later.

11:10.280 --> 11:11.872
(ENGINE STARTS)

11:25.400 --> 11:26.799
UNCLE SIMON:
So, what's the problem?

11:26.880 --> 11:30.190
MELEA: My tuition is overdue, and I
can't return to class until it's paid.

11:30.280 --> 11:32.032
And what about
your scholarships?

11:32.960 --> 11:34.359
Not enough.

11:36.240 --> 11:38.595
And you weren't
going to tell me?

11:39.800 --> 11:42.678
I mean, you already let me stay here.
You put food on the table.

11:42.760 --> 11:44.671
The least I can
do is handle this.

11:46.280 --> 11:50.353
Melea, you know I will do
anything to help you.

11:50.760 --> 11:52.830
But you have to talk to me.

11:55.640 --> 11:57.790
Well, you know I promised Mom
that I would get my degree.

11:58.760 --> 12:02.070
Ever since I started doing this
Romeo and Juliet thesis...

12:02.640 --> 12:03.629
Phew.

12:03.960 --> 12:06.952
I thought it was the perfect
way to honor her memory.

12:07.760 --> 12:12.595
I'm pretty sure that giving up is
a lousy way to honor your mother.

12:13.960 --> 12:15.552
You're probably right.

12:15.800 --> 12:18.234
And I'm pretty sure
you're gonna beat this.

12:18.320 --> 12:20.515
(SCOFFS)
What makes you so sure?

12:22.000 --> 12:23.991
I screwed everything
up so much already.

12:24.080 --> 12:27.197
Well, you're a smart young lady.
And that's important.

12:28.080 --> 12:31.959
But mostly, you're very
stubborn and thick-headed.

12:32.520 --> 12:33.953
Gee, thanks. (CHUCKLES)

12:34.800 --> 12:38.475
I think we need to do less
talking and more eating.

12:38.760 --> 12:40.193
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

12:40.800 --> 12:43.155
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

12:43.280 --> 12:44.872
ERIK: What are you gonna do?

12:44.960 --> 12:47.633
MELEA: I'm gonna get a job,
figure it out.

12:47.920 --> 12:48.989
How?

12:50.240 --> 12:52.470
I don't know.
I'll find a space.

12:52.920 --> 12:54.319
I'll mount it myself.

12:54.520 --> 12:56.556
I don't know why it's
so important to you.

12:56.640 --> 12:59.200
'Cause I have
something to say, Erik.

12:59.560 --> 13:01.471
'Cause Romeo and
Juliet hasn't been done

13:01.560 --> 13:03.596
in the way that
I want to do it.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.468
And dance is the way I speak.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.309
I want to be able
to tell this story,

13:10.400 --> 13:12.277
and have it reach
out to people.

13:13.520 --> 13:15.590
It's my mom's favorite play, and
I want to honor her with it.

13:15.680 --> 13:16.669
You will.

13:17.520 --> 13:19.476
Why does it have
to be right now?

13:19.720 --> 13:21.756
I mean, I get it. I'm the
same way with my music,

13:21.840 --> 13:25.833
but I think you need to focus on
money and getting back into school,

13:25.920 --> 13:28.354
and then worry
about your show.

13:29.000 --> 13:30.353
(SIGHS)

13:30.440 --> 13:32.510
I'm gonna figure
out a way to do both.

13:33.440 --> 13:36.034
And costumes, and sets.
It's not cheap.

13:36.120 --> 13:37.997
How're you gonna
afford all that?

13:39.800 --> 13:42.109
Ticket sales, eventually. Oh!

13:42.200 --> 13:46.113
Um... And you're still gonna
help me with the music, right?

13:46.520 --> 13:47.475
You're serious?

13:47.560 --> 13:49.198
I'm dead serious.

13:49.440 --> 13:52.034
But if you pull this off,
then, yes, I'll do the music.

13:53.000 --> 13:54.149
Great.

13:54.360 --> 13:55.998
Now, all I have
to do is find a job,

13:56.040 --> 13:58.156
so I can afford paper to print tickets.
(LAUGHS)

13:58.240 --> 14:00.549
Wish me luck.
Yeah, you don't need it.

14:00.960 --> 14:05.636
And look, if all else fails, I
mean, at least you got Romeo.

14:06.160 --> 14:08.230
(CHUCKLES) You can
be so corny sometimes.

14:08.320 --> 14:10.550
Yeah, that was corny. All
right, I'm out of here. Bye.

14:30.840 --> 14:32.717
Hello.
My name is Melea Martin.

14:32.800 --> 14:33.994
I'm a hip-hop choreographer,

14:34.080 --> 14:36.833
and I'm interested in interviewing
for your open position.

14:36.920 --> 14:40.310
MAN: Hip-hop? Oh, no. We only
teach ballet and jazz here.

14:45.520 --> 14:47.511
(MUSIC PLAYING)

15:26.480 --> 15:28.436
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

15:28.520 --> 15:29.509
(CUTLERY CLATTERS)

15:39.520 --> 15:41.317
(MUSIC PLAYING)

15:55.160 --> 15:57.151
Okay, I see you. Get it.

15:58.560 --> 15:59.834
Oh, you like what you see?

16:00.840 --> 16:02.319
Come and get some.

16:02.920 --> 16:04.478
Oh, it's like that? Okay.

16:04.560 --> 16:05.549
Whoo!

16:07.560 --> 16:09.994
Oh, Crystal, you do not want
to mess with my friend.

16:10.680 --> 16:12.398
Melea is no joke.

16:12.760 --> 16:14.034
Yeah, right. (SCOFFS)

16:14.960 --> 16:16.552
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

16:16.640 --> 16:19.108
Okay, everybody,
get back to class now.

16:19.200 --> 16:20.519
I don't want
anyone being late.

16:20.920 --> 16:23.753
Go hit those books
like you hit those moves.

16:25.200 --> 16:26.349
Zam, you, too.

16:27.880 --> 16:30.155
I've seen you before.
You are good.

16:30.240 --> 16:31.389
(CHUCKLES) Thank you.

16:36.040 --> 16:38.998
Wow! You really impressed him.

16:39.080 --> 16:42.038
That was his version of rambling.
He never says anything.

16:42.360 --> 16:43.588
He seems like a cool kid.

16:43.720 --> 16:45.950
Oh, he is.
He's just hard to reach.

16:46.040 --> 16:47.155
Hmm.

16:47.240 --> 16:48.832
What are you doing today?

16:48.920 --> 16:52.390
Oh, just a job search, but
they don't have anything here.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.319
Yeah, budget cuts.

16:54.400 --> 16:55.594
Why the need for
money all of a sudden?

16:55.680 --> 16:56.829
For school.

16:56.920 --> 17:00.674
All my scholarships ran out.
And now they want cash.

17:01.360 --> 17:04.238
Welcome to the real world.
Tell me about it.

17:04.560 --> 17:06.152
Okay, well,
I better get inside

17:06.240 --> 17:07.877
before my students
form a coup. Good luck.

17:07.960 --> 17:08.994
Okay, thank you.
Call me.

17:09.079 --> 17:10.194
All right.
Ooh, give me my phone?

17:10.520 --> 17:12.271
Oh, shoot,
I almost forgot.

17:13.319 --> 17:15.310
Here you are. Bye.
Thanks, girl.

17:20.560 --> 17:21.628
Don't ever give up.

17:21.720 --> 17:22.789
Hey, yo, check it.

17:28.560 --> 17:31.154
What happened?
You playing hooky?

17:31.240 --> 17:33.117
(CHUCKLES) Not that
it's any of your business,

17:33.200 --> 17:34.758
but I'm taking
a break from school.

17:34.920 --> 17:35.955
Oh!

17:36.040 --> 17:40.352
So, now you back in the hood.
Bumped down to our level.

17:40.440 --> 17:41.429
(CHUCKLES)

17:41.520 --> 17:43.909
For your information,
I live in this neighborhood.

17:44.040 --> 17:45.758
I don't consider
it a bump-down.

17:45.960 --> 17:47.109
What's your name, girl?

17:48.120 --> 17:50.076
Was gonna ask you
the same thing.

17:50.160 --> 17:53.152
I'm Ishani.
Everybody knows me.

17:53.240 --> 17:55.356
(LAUGHS)

17:55.440 --> 17:56.873
I'm Melea.

17:56.960 --> 17:58.757
And you should get to know me
before you judge me.

17:59.160 --> 18:02.118
So, what? You want to have me
over for tea or something?

18:02.200 --> 18:04.555
(ALL LAUGH)
ISHANI: This girl's a trip.

18:05.160 --> 18:06.309
Everything all right, Melea?

18:07.760 --> 18:09.637
MELEA: Yeah, Taariq.
We're cool.

18:13.400 --> 18:16.631
If you're looking for friends,
go back to America,

18:16.720 --> 18:18.631
'cause you won't
find them here.

18:20.480 --> 18:22.869
Come on, let's go.
We got better things to do.

18:22.960 --> 18:24.871
Yeah.
She's a waste of time.

18:24.960 --> 18:26.996
(MUSIC PLAYING)

18:42.960 --> 18:44.996
Where to?
MELEA: Bo-Kaap.

18:45.520 --> 18:46.714
Bo-Kaap.

19:30.920 --> 19:32.956
You know,
I don't need security.

19:33.040 --> 19:34.837
(CHUCKLES)
Are you sure about that?

19:36.200 --> 19:38.191
We just came here
to dance, man.

19:41.560 --> 19:43.676
(MUSIC PLAYING)

19:54.320 --> 19:55.594
Yo, yo! 'Sup, boys?

19:56.320 --> 19:57.469
Yo, what's up?
Boy!

19:57.560 --> 19:58.993
Yo, what's happening?

19:59.080 --> 20:00.877
(INDISTINCT GREETING)

20:01.480 --> 20:02.469
MAN: What's up?

20:02.560 --> 20:03.675
(MELEA LAUGHS)

20:03.760 --> 20:05.955
Yeah, go! Hit it!

20:11.480 --> 20:12.595
Yeah!

20:24.960 --> 20:28.077
I like your style, Taariq. It's
pretty dope. I'll catch you later.

20:30.640 --> 20:33.234
Peace, Taariq.
You guys are great.

20:33.320 --> 20:34.958
Thank you.
Yeah! Sweet.

20:35.040 --> 20:36.598
All right, let's do it.

20:42.800 --> 20:45.394
You are making the best decision, Mr.
Wright.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.797
Well, I sure hope so.

20:51.280 --> 20:52.395
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

20:52.520 --> 20:53.919
Mr. Wright.
Yes?

20:54.000 --> 20:56.912
Oh, my goodness.
It's Melea. Isn't it?

20:57.000 --> 20:58.672
Yeah, I can't believe
you remember me.

20:58.760 --> 21:00.751
Well, you look
just like your mother.

21:00.840 --> 21:03.070
How's she doing?
Is she with you?

21:03.440 --> 21:06.910
Um, no. She passed.
About a year ago.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.719
Oh, Lord. I am sorry.

21:11.120 --> 21:13.076
She was one fine lady.

21:13.160 --> 21:15.037
Yeah, she was.

21:15.920 --> 21:18.798
Hey, I wanted to talk to you
about working here at Bijou.

21:19.200 --> 21:20.792
Is there anything I
can do around here?

21:20.880 --> 21:22.393
Melea, you're too late.

21:22.920 --> 21:25.878
The lady who
just left, uh, Miss Lee,

21:25.960 --> 21:27.632
she's thinking
of buying the place.

21:29.520 --> 21:31.988
