40:04.200 --> 40:06.350
Do you really know
what this play is about?

40:06.440 --> 40:07.793
ALL: No.

40:07.880 --> 40:09.677
That's what I thought.
Sit down.

40:12.440 --> 40:14.954
All right, so I'm gonna
give you the lowdown.

40:15.040 --> 40:17.873
So, the Capulets
are Juliet's parents.

40:18.720 --> 40:20.597
They don't get along
with Romeo's parents.

40:20.680 --> 40:25.276
You guys hate each other. It's kind
of like rival gangs in The Flats.

40:25.400 --> 40:27.391
(MUSIC PLAYING)

40:30.600 --> 40:33.353
Everyone knows
the basic plot of the story.

40:34.520 --> 40:37.432
Boy and girl fall in love,
and die in the end.

40:40.080 --> 40:42.150
But it's so much
more than that.

40:48.840 --> 40:53.709
It's a story of forbidden love surrounded
by violence, revenge, and death.

40:54.920 --> 40:59.835
People died basically for no reason,
just like here in The Flats.

41:06.680 --> 41:09.353
And Juliet is in
the middle of it all.

41:09.440 --> 41:12.318
Alone, confused, and afraid.

41:17.280 --> 41:20.795
So, Benvolio and Mercutio,
they're Romeo's friends.

41:20.880 --> 41:24.555
And they get into it with
Tybalt, who is Juliet's cousin.

41:24.640 --> 41:25.755
He's one badass dude.

41:25.840 --> 41:27.432
(ALL CHUCKLING)

41:28.040 --> 41:29.632
Our version of the story opens

41:29.720 --> 41:32.154
on a big rumble
between the families.

41:32.240 --> 41:35.277
Everyone's fighting like it's a
Saturday night in The Flats.

41:35.360 --> 41:37.157
And these fights are sick.

41:37.240 --> 41:39.390
During one of the fights,
Romeo ends up getting killed

41:39.480 --> 41:41.471
by Juliet's
badass cousin, Tybalt.

41:41.600 --> 41:43.272
Eventually,
Romeo gets run out of town

41:43.360 --> 41:44.998
and that makes
things much worse.

41:45.080 --> 41:48.038
But during our
opening fight, this cop,

41:48.120 --> 41:49.633
better known as
the Prince of Verona,

41:49.720 --> 41:51.551
shows up and
breaks up the fight.

41:55.560 --> 41:57.312
He tells them that
the next guy to start a fight

41:57.400 --> 41:59.516
is gonna be punished
with death.

42:00.040 --> 42:01.871
So, they all scatter.

42:03.320 --> 42:05.356
But let's get back to the
Capulets and the Montagues.

42:06.720 --> 42:09.359
Juliet's parents are
talking to this guy, Paris.

42:09.800 --> 42:11.631
He's one of their own,

42:11.720 --> 42:14.632
but he's just a rich guy
that's got his eye on Juliet.

42:14.760 --> 42:16.751
(ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING)

42:22.760 --> 42:24.273
And right then and there,

42:24.360 --> 42:27.591
they tell her that she has to marry
the guy, without even asking.

42:29.240 --> 42:32.391
So, they send out
invites for a party

42:32.480 --> 42:34.152
to get the two
of them together,

42:34.280 --> 42:36.077
and it's Capulets only.

42:51.400 --> 42:55.188
And my man, Romeo, shows up,
steals the invite,

42:55.280 --> 42:58.397
and has the bright idea
of crashing the party.

42:58.480 --> 43:00.710
That's where he meets Juliet.

43:01.280 --> 43:03.475
And it's love at first sight.

43:05.720 --> 43:08.109
And that, folks,
is just the beginning.

43:08.520 --> 43:09.953
Yeah!

43:11.080 --> 43:12.115
Yes.

43:12.200 --> 43:13.792
I like it.
(GIGGLES)

43:14.840 --> 43:15.829
Bye, Melea.
Bye.

43:15.920 --> 43:17.239
Great stuff today.
Yeah, you, too.

43:17.320 --> 43:18.753
Thank you. Thank you.

43:18.800 --> 43:20.870
All right, see you soon.
Bye, see you soon.

43:20.960 --> 43:23.474
Bye, girl.
Bye.

43:23.560 --> 43:24.709
See you later.
Bye.

43:24.800 --> 43:26.028
Melea?

43:26.120 --> 43:29.396
Just wanted to tell you I'm proud of you.
You're doing a great job.

43:29.520 --> 43:31.909
Thank you, Mr. Diego.
You're welcome.

43:32.000 --> 43:34.594
And I think you can
call me Eduardo now.

43:34.680 --> 43:37.319
Especially since you're in charge.
(BOTH LAUGH)

43:37.520 --> 43:38.748
Thanks. (CLICKS TONGUE)

43:39.240 --> 43:42.118
But I just can't shake the feeling
that I'm missing something.

43:42.200 --> 43:43.952
The piece needs more.

43:44.960 --> 43:47.269
Edge.
Yes.

43:47.360 --> 43:49.874
A lot of shows have
more than one choreographer.

43:49.960 --> 43:53.316
You need someone with a fresh set of eyes.
A different flair.

43:54.000 --> 43:59.154
Someone with a raw passion. You
find them, and this show will sing.

43:59.960 --> 44:01.359
Thank you.

44:09.320 --> 44:11.550
(MUSIC PLAYING)

44:17.640 --> 44:19.358
TAJ: Yes, you said it.

44:19.800 --> 44:21.916
ISHANI: Really?
TAJ: Yeah.

44:22.000 --> 44:23.672
I've been spending time there.

44:23.760 --> 44:26.479
I just think you could find something
better to do with your time.

44:26.600 --> 44:30.673
Ishani, you keep telling me I could
do so much to help The Flats,

44:30.760 --> 44:34.070
and now that I'm doing it,
you're still not happy.

44:34.160 --> 44:36.196
(SCOFFS) How is helping that
American chick helping us?

44:36.280 --> 44:38.589
Whoa!
Forget I'm American, too?

44:38.680 --> 44:39.999
Not like her.

44:41.440 --> 44:44.352
Look, Melea's got
a lot of kids dancing for her.

44:44.440 --> 44:46.476
Kids who would usually
be out on the streets

44:46.560 --> 44:48.516
getting into trouble
like your...

44:50.240 --> 44:52.993
I'm... Yo, I'm... I'm sorry.

44:53.080 --> 44:54.718
Yeah, you should be.

45:04.200 --> 45:05.997
Rented out a private...

45:06.080 --> 45:07.513
Probably, yes.

45:15.560 --> 45:17.596
Great, right on cue.

45:18.080 --> 45:19.877
Sniffing around
for Taj, I guess.

45:20.240 --> 45:21.992
No, I was actually
coming to see you.

45:22.080 --> 45:24.799
Girl, you need to stay out of
my face before I hurt you.

45:25.120 --> 45:26.314
NADINE: MeMe.

45:26.400 --> 45:27.799
Hey, you made it.

45:27.880 --> 45:29.677
Yeah, I came
to talk to Ishani.

45:30.360 --> 45:32.157
Oh. The kind of talk
where I need

45:32.240 --> 45:34.390
to take off my
shoes and earrings?

45:34.480 --> 45:36.675
Wasn't planning on it.
That's on Ishani.

45:36.760 --> 45:39.274
You need to leave before
you both get a beatdown.

45:39.960 --> 45:41.552
(CHUCKLES) Okay, girl.

45:42.040 --> 45:43.871
You're not the only one
with friends around here.

45:45.720 --> 45:47.756
Okay, you guys, it's
not going down like that.

45:47.840 --> 45:48.829
Mm.

45:50.760 --> 45:53.399
You need to accept the fact
that I'm not scared of you.

45:53.520 --> 45:55.078
You should be.

45:55.640 --> 45:56.868
Whatever.

45:56.960 --> 45:58.518
Look, I need you
to work on my show.

45:58.920 --> 45:59.989
What?

46:01.240 --> 46:03.071
(CHUCKLES) No, thanks.

46:03.960 --> 46:05.234
Why not?

46:07.040 --> 46:09.031
Do you have
something better to do?

46:09.160 --> 46:11.879
I know your type,
and you're not gonna play me.

46:11.960 --> 46:14.394
You put on a show,
and when it's over,

46:14.480 --> 46:17.790
you take off back to America,
and we're still here.

46:17.920 --> 46:23.153
Nothing changes. No jobs, no
money, no hope, nowhere to go.

46:23.240 --> 46:26.312
Kids getting killed
over a goddamn necklace.

46:32.600 --> 46:35.068
So, what would you suggest?
What would work for you?

46:35.160 --> 46:36.718
What would make you happy?

46:36.800 --> 46:38.233
I don't know.

46:38.880 --> 46:41.917
Maybe a rec center,
or a dance hall.

46:43.240 --> 46:46.312
Some place a kid could go and
do something besides drugs.

46:48.600 --> 46:49.669
Then let's do it.

46:50.320 --> 46:52.311
And there's that
"save the world" shit.

46:52.400 --> 46:53.753
(CHUCKLES)

46:53.840 --> 46:56.274
I'm serious.
Let's make a difference.

46:57.680 --> 47:00.638
You don't have to stop
at one night, one show.

47:01.480 --> 47:02.754
I want to help.

47:04.320 --> 47:05.673
Are you in?

47:11.080 --> 47:14.038
There's love in the house!
Yeah, baby!

47:14.360 --> 47:16.351
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

47:21.080 --> 47:22.593
MELEA:
Hey, heads up, everybody.

47:22.680 --> 47:25.797
This is our new
co-choreographer, Ishani Mfeke.

47:26.080 --> 47:28.799
She will also be dancing
the role of Tybalt,

47:28.880 --> 47:30.757
so if you think
she ain't man enough,

47:30.840 --> 47:32.910
I'd watch my back
if I were you.

47:33.560 --> 47:36.393
Well, Melea.
You sure this is a good idea?

47:37.080 --> 47:39.958
No, but I haven't been sure of
anything since I started this.

47:40.040 --> 47:41.109
(CLICKS TONGUE)
Okay.

47:42.200 --> 47:43.315
But I'm watching you.

47:45.800 --> 47:47.677
(MELEA CHUCKLES)
Okay, guys, let's set it off.

47:50.560 --> 47:53.677
And make sure to
hit this hard, okay?

47:55.000 --> 47:57.036
(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

48:23.280 --> 48:24.918
MELEA: All right, get low.

48:25.000 --> 48:27.355
And five, six, seven, eight.

48:27.440 --> 48:33.595
And one, and two, and three, and
four, and five, six, seven, eight.

48:33.880 --> 48:39.159
And one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, and eight.

48:39.760 --> 48:41.796
All right, hit it from the top.
ALL: All right.

48:41.880 --> 48:43.871
(MUSIC PLAYING)

49:01.320 --> 49:02.309
(SIGHS)

49:03.400 --> 49:05.595
See, now, that's old school.

49:05.720 --> 49:09.315
Think you have something better?
If they can bring it.

49:09.400 --> 49:13.154
Well, that's what you're here for.
Go out there and show 'em.

49:13.240 --> 49:14.753
No problem.

49:14.840 --> 49:16.319
Follow my lead.

49:16.400 --> 49:18.391
(CHEERING AND CHATTERING)

49:23.040 --> 49:25.270
Five, six, seven, eight.

49:57.440 --> 49:58.509
NADINE: Damn.

49:59.000 --> 50:00.592
She's good.
Hmm.

50:01.560 --> 50:02.879
I'm not gonna tell
her that, though.

50:03.920 --> 50:06.354
It's okay. She already knows.
(CHUCKLES)

50:08.640 --> 50:10.995
And five, six, seven, eight.

50:16.880 --> 50:18.950
What's up?
Hi, how are you?

50:19.040 --> 50:20.314
Good.

50:20.400 --> 50:22.277
I see you guys
are hard at it.

50:22.880 --> 50:24.518
It's going well.

50:25.280 --> 50:27.396
You have something
for me?

50:27.480 --> 50:30.995
Not yet, but I listened
to your boyfriend's track,

50:31.080 --> 50:32.832
and I'm gonna
lace it with lyrics.

50:32.920 --> 50:35.798
Might want to tell him to add a
horn, just to kick it up a bit.

50:35.880 --> 50:37.677
I will. Thank you.

50:39.320 --> 50:42.630
MELEA: Your girl over there is amazing.
TAJ: Yeah, I know.

50:44.920 --> 50:46.194
She's not my girl.

50:47.080 --> 50:48.718
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

50:49.240 --> 50:50.229
Hmm.

50:50.320 --> 50:51.514
Hmm?
(CHUCKLES)

50:51.600 --> 50:53.079
What was that?

51:12.400 --> 51:14.436
(MUSIC PLAYING)

51:53.640 --> 51:54.675
Whoa!

51:55.280 --> 51:56.554
Hey, MeMe?

51:56.640 --> 51:57.629
What?

51:57.760 --> 51:59.557
Come here. We got a problem.

52:01.160 --> 52:02.479
What's up?

52:03.000 --> 52:05.389
Tickets aren't selling
as fast as we had hoped.

52:05.480 --> 52:07.789
At this rate,
we won't have a full house.

52:07.880 --> 52:10.235
That's not an option.
We have to sell out.

52:10.320 --> 52:13.198
We have to make enough
to pay rent on the rec center.

52:13.920 --> 52:15.831
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

52:17.360 --> 52:21.069
Melea, this is my mama
and my sister, Kiara.

52:21.200 --> 52:24.397
Pleased to meet you,
Mrs. Mfeke. Kiara.

52:25.240 --> 52:27.196
They're both seamstresses,

52:27.280 --> 52:29.157
so Mama was thinking
they could help out

52:29.240 --> 52:30.753
with the costumes
we still need.

52:30.840 --> 52:32.114
That would be great.

52:32.200 --> 52:33.599
Let me show you
what I borrowed

52:33.680 --> 52:35.113
from the college's
wardrobe department.

52:35.480 --> 52:36.674
(KIARA CHUCKLES)

52:39.200 --> 52:40.189
Um...

52:41.440 --> 52:44.796
I truly appreciate you giving
'Shani this opportunity.

52:46.440 --> 52:48.192
She's been needing
something like this.

52:48.880 --> 52:50.438
They both have.

52:50.560 --> 52:53.916
I couldn't do it without her,
believe me. Thank you.

52:55.840 --> 52:58.559
I think Juliet's family
should wear red.

52:58.960 --> 53:00.393
MELEA: Sounds great.

53:01.680 --> 53:03.238
ISHANI: Everyone take five.

53:04.120 --> 53:07.430
Melea, can I talk to you?
What's up?

53:08.640 --> 53:10.915
You know the whole Romeo
and Juliet theme? Hmm.

53:11.040 --> 53:14.032
It's all about the dumb stuff
people pull, beginning to end.

53:14.640 --> 53:16.949
Yeah, but in this scene,
these guys are family.

53:17.640 --> 53:18.914
So, they don't act dumb?

53:19.880 --> 53:22.440
You ever been to a party
and someone wasn't acting out?

53:23.120 --> 53:25.839
Not lately, no.
Exactly.

53:25.920 --> 53:28.150
Even the ladies should be
trying to one-up each other.

53:28.240 --> 53:30.071
Like when we first met.

53:30.600 --> 53:32.079
So, what you're saying is...

53:32.680 --> 53:34.955
Get over here.
Let's show 'em how it's done.

53:35.480 --> 53:36.515
Okay.

53:37.160 --> 53:39.549
Zam, give us something
we can work with.

53:39.640 --> 53:41.631
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

53:43.280 --> 53:44.269
What you want?

53:49.760 --> 53:50.954
Quit playing around.

53:51.080 --> 53:53.036
Come on, let's bring it.
You ready? (LAUGHS)

54:24.560 --> 54:25.595
Whoo!

54:25.680 --> 54:26.749
(CHUCKLES) Yes!

54:26.840 --> 54:27.989
That's what I'm talkin' about.

54:30.800 --> 54:33.792
You pushed Juliet, and she pushed back.
I love that.

54:33.880 --> 54:36.440
Okay. That was hot.

54:37.920 --> 54:39.558
You're okay by me.

54:39.640 --> 54:41.551
(CHUCKLES) Man,
you girls are soft.

54:42.360 --> 54:43.679
You love it.

54:44.520 --> 54:46.590
(ALL GIGGLING)

54:47.840 --> 54:49.876
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

55:09.320 --> 55:11.754
And five, six, seven, eight.

55:11.840 --> 55:13.876
(MUSIC PLAYING)

55:17.200 --> 55:18.474
Cue Romeo.

55:24.360 --> 55:25.873
Really get into it.

55:27.480 --> 55:28.708
Feel it.

55:31.080 --> 55:32.069
(DAJON GROANS)

55:33.320 --> 55:35.390
ISHANI: Dajon, are you all right?
DAJON: Mm-mm.

55:37.240 --> 55:38.468
It was an accident.

55:38.560 --> 55:39.913
I'm sorry, man.
It's okay.

55:40.000 --> 55:41.319
Don't... It's okay.

55:41.440 --> 55:42.668
Just need...
Oh, no!

55:42.760 --> 55:43.829
MELEA: No, it's not okay.

55:43.920 --> 55:45.399
We have to get
you to a hospital.

55:45.480 --> 55:47.436
I'll take him.
My car's out front.

55:48.480 --> 55:49.993
(DAJON WINCING)

55:57.240 --> 55:59.390
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENTS)

56:01.240 --> 56:03.231
MELEA: Eduardo, how is he?

56:04.280 --> 56:05.474
It's fractured.

56:07.880 --> 56:10.758
You're definitely
gonna need another Romeo.

56:16.840 --> 56:18.193
I need you.

56:20.600 --> 56:22.591
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

56:56.840 --> 56:58.956
(APPLAUSE)

57:01.360 --> 57:02.349
Whoo!

57:04.280 --> 57:05.429
Yeah.
Yeah.

57:05.640 --> 57:08.632
That was good,
but that song gotta go.

57:09.640 --> 57:11.949
What are you talking about?
I thought it was perfect.

57:12.960 --> 57:15.679
Really? Do you think
that's the best he can do?

57:16.160 --> 57:18.993
Let me guess. You got
something better in mind?

57:19.120 --> 57:20.792
As a matter of fact,
I do, man.

57:20.880 --> 57:22.199
Yeah.

57:22.280 --> 57:23.713
Play it, Zam.

57:24.320 --> 57:26.356
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

57:32.600 --> 57:33.589
Whoo!

57:34.720 --> 57:35.709
Whoo!

57:47.560 --> 57:50.120
Now, that's something new I've
been working on for you, Melea.

57:50.200 --> 57:51.997
Because I think
you can do better.

57:53.680 --> 57:54.874
Are you kidding me?

57:54.960 --> 57:56.234
You know,
I'm gettin' really sick

57:56.320 --> 57:57.469
of you running your
mouth all the time.

57:57.560 --> 57:58.788
Shut up, man.
What?

57:59.680 --> 58:00.749
Stop it!

58:00.840 --> 58:03.035
No, no, no.
Stay out of this, Ishani.

58:03.120 --> 58:04.553
It's between me and him.

58:04.640 --> 58:06.392
What, I'm stupid?

58:06.480 --> 58:08.869
I'm not.
You're fighting over Melea.

58:08.960 --> 58:10.109
What?

58:10.200 --> 58:11.952
We're fighting over the music.

58:12.040 --> 58:13.519
Music? I'm fighting
over my girlfriend.

58:13.640 --> 58:14.993
What... What? No...
Then stop it.

58:15.080 --> 58:18.709
This is insane. Come on, Taj is
just trying to help, you guys.

58:18.800 --> 58:19.949
Melea, don't be stupid.

58:20.680 --> 58:24.355
You said it yourself.
He can have any girl he wants.

58:24.440 --> 58:25.555
And he wants you.

58:27.120 --> 58:28.189
Hey, Ishani.

58:28.280 --> 58:29.759
Ishani, wait.

58:36.960 --> 58:38.359
Hey, where are you going?

58:38.440 --> 58:39.475
Anywhere.

58:39.560 --> 58:41.755
Away from here, away from him.

58:42.400 --> 58:45.278
Ishani, look at me.
I'm not into Taj.

58:45.360 --> 58:48.193
I'm in love with Erik. Besides,
I wouldn't do that to you.

58:48.280 --> 58:49.474
I know how much you like him.

58:49.560 --> 58:50.788
Do you?

58:50.920 --> 58:53.309
(CHUCKLES) Look, I'm not
playing this game with you.

58:53.400 --> 58:57.075
We both know you want Taj. You're
always throwing yourself at him.

58:57.840 --> 59:00.354
I'm not gonna be a decoy so you
can cheat on your boyfriend.

59:00.440 --> 59:01.429
What?

59:01.520 --> 59:03.078
What are you talking about?
Are you crazy?

59:03.160 --> 59:05.037
Yeah. Yeah, I'm crazy.

59:05.600 --> 59:07.158
Crazy for letting
my guard down

59:07.240 --> 59:09.231
with a girl who's used to
getting whatever she wants.

59:09.600 --> 59:12.433
Crazy to get involved
with you, this show.

59:13.080 --> 59:15.150
Good luck with your
fantasy world, Melea.

59:15.280 --> 59:17.271
I'm going back
to the real one.

59:24.560 --> 59:25.595
Hey.

59:26.720 --> 59:28.597
Look, I just want to
let you know that I'm done.

59:29.160 --> 59:30.718
I'm done with us,
I'm done with the show.

59:30.800 --> 59:32.677
If I'm not gonna be
your Romeo in real life,

59:32.760 --> 59:34.591
why am I gonna be
him in your musical?

59:35.800 --> 59:37.074
I just need a break,
all right?

59:37.160 --> 59:39.355
I'm gonna focus on myself.
That's what I'm gonna do.

59:39.440 --> 59:41.431
Erik...
No. Bye, Melea.

59:44.480 --> 59:45.469
(SCOFFS)

01:00:11.160 --> 01:00:12.275
MeMe.

01:00:13.760 --> 01:00:14.829
Hey.

01:00:15.440 --> 01:00:16.793
Hey, girl.

01:00:17.960 --> 01:00:19.916
So sorry about all this.

01:00:20.480 --> 01:00:21.879
But I think it's a sign.

01:00:23.680 --> 01:00:27.355
Erik said he's out.
Tickets are just not moving.

01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:28.589
Mm-mm.

01:00:28.680 --> 01:00:30.955
Can't make this happen
out of thin air.

01:00:31.760 --> 01:00:36.390
So, I think we need to regroup and try
and make this work at another time.

01:00:37.440 --> 01:00:38.589
Okay, baby girl?

01:00:42.760 --> 01:00:45.593
Wait, Erik didn't bail
on you as well, did he?

01:00:46.840 --> 01:00:50.071
Look, I don't want to talk about it.
I'm cool.

01:00:50.760 --> 01:00:52.193
Hit me later?

01:00:55.560 --> 01:00:56.549
(KISSES)

01:01:00.680 --> 01:01:01.715
(SIGHS)

01:01:27.520 --> 01:01:29.556
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:48.871
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

01:03:21.000 --> 01:03:22.991
(PANTING)

01:03:27.560 --> 01:03:29.676
(CAR ENGINE REVVS)

01:03:34.800 --> 01:03:35.789
Get in.

01:03:37.200 --> 01:03:38.838
(CLICKS TONGUE) I'm not
going anywhere with you.

01:03:42.520 --> 01:03:43.953
Girl, I said get in.

01:03:51.200 --> 01:03:52.838
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:04:19.640 --> 01:04:20.993
(SEATBELT BUCKLE CLICKS)

01:04:24.360 --> 01:04:25.475
What is your problem?

01:04:25.560 --> 01:04:27.471
I don't have a problem.

01:04:27.560 --> 01:04:30.313
You're the one hung up on a girl
who doesn't care about you.

01:04:30.400 --> 01:04:34.154
Strutting around here like a fool,
and she ain't even into you.

01:04:34.240 --> 01:04:36.834
You're right. She's not.

01:04:38.240 --> 01:04:41.232
I guess being rich and famous
doesn't work on everybody, huh?

01:04:50.320 --> 01:04:51.833
Apparently not.

01:04:52.840 --> 01:04:54.353
(SEATBELT BUCKLE CLICKS)

01:05:04.480 --> 01:05:06.471
Let me ask you somethin'.

01:05:07.080 --> 01:05:08.354
Why'd you get so mad?

01:05:08.440 --> 01:05:13.195
Because I'm your friend, and I
was just looking out for you.

01:05:14.200 --> 01:05:15.428
Is that all?

01:05:15.520 --> 01:05:16.635
Yeah.

01:05:18.160 --> 01:05:22.199
Damn, that's too bad,
because, um, you're right.

01:05:23.080 --> 01:05:27.119
I am crazy about this girl and she
acts like I don't even exist.

01:05:28.120 --> 01:05:31.112
That's too bad. Maybe you
should give up on her.

01:05:31.200 --> 01:05:32.952
I don't think I can do that.

01:05:34.080 --> 01:05:35.991
Not when I'm
this close to her.

01:05:36.720 --> 01:05:37.789
What?

01:05:39.680 --> 01:05:43.468
Ishani, I'm hung up on
somebody, but it's not Melea.

01:05:44.240 --> 01:05:45.355
It's you.

01:05:46.080 --> 01:05:48.640
Taj, don't play with me.
I'm not.

01:05:48.720 --> 01:05:51.632
Why do you think I come back
here every chance I get?

01:05:52.640 --> 01:05:54.358
Ishani, I come to see you.

01:05:55.520 --> 01:05:58.353
I don't believe you.
You've never said anything.

01:05:58.440 --> 01:06:00.670
Because I didn't want
to ruin our friendship.

01:06:00.760 --> 01:06:01.749
And then, your brother...

01:06:06.160 --> 01:06:08.628
Hey, Ishani, look at me.

01:06:09.680 --> 01:06:12.069
I'm tired of waiting
and playing games.

01:06:12.160 --> 01:06:14.071
I bought a house
to impress you.

01:06:14.160 --> 01:06:16.674
I got involved
with the community.

01:06:16.880 --> 01:06:18.598
Now, I'm just
gonna flat-out say it.

01:06:18.680 --> 01:06:20.079
Ishani, I love...

01:06:24.160 --> 01:06:25.195
Me, too.

01:06:27.080 --> 01:06:29.036
Yeah?
Yeah.

01:06:36.120 --> 01:06:37.109
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

01:06:38.840 --> 01:06:39.909
Hey, Erik.

01:06:41.520 --> 01:06:43.112
We need to talk.

01:06:49.880 --> 01:06:51.518
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:06:53.040 --> 01:06:55.429
(ZUBAIR SPEAKS IN NATIVE
LANGUAGE OVER RADIO)

01:06:55.520 --> 01:06:56.555
This is Zubair Khumalo,

01:06:56.640 --> 01:06:59.598
and we are live from GoodHope
FM studios in Cape Town.

01:06:59.680 --> 01:07:00.795
We got Taj in the studio,

01:07:00.880 --> 01:07:03.633
and Taj has got a brand-new
album coming out this year,

01:07:03.720 --> 01:07:05.995
and he's got something
very interesting as well.

01:07:06.080 --> 01:07:07.115
Tell us
about it, dawg.

01:07:07.200 --> 01:07:09.316
Yeah, man. A hip-hop
performance

01:07:09.400 --> 01:07:11.277
of Romeo and Juliet.

01:07:27.240 --> 01:07:29.276
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

01:07:30.600 --> 01:07:32.192
Ishani, where have you been?

01:07:32.280 --> 01:07:35.477
ISHANI: Shut up.
Put on the radio. 94.0.

01:07:36.280 --> 01:07:37.315
What?

01:07:37.560 --> 01:07:39.835
Just do it. 94.0.

01:07:42.400 --> 01:07:43.833
ZUBAIR: That is radical, man.

01:07:43.920 --> 01:07:44.989
So, musically, what?

01:07:45.120 --> 01:07:46.997
All right, are you merging
the two worlds together

01:07:47.080 --> 01:07:48.195
like a yin and a yang?

01:07:48.280 --> 01:07:49.235
Yeah, yeah, yeah,

01:07:49.320 --> 01:07:50.719
but I can't take
all of the credit.

01:07:51.120 --> 01:07:54.351
This is a passion project of Melea Martin.
A'ight? (CHUCKLES)

01:07:54.440 --> 01:07:56.271
And I got my man here with me,
Erik Wildwood,

01:07:56.360 --> 01:07:59.796
and we did a collabo' together
to make it super-dope.

01:07:59.880 --> 01:08:01.074
Yo, tell 'em, E.

01:08:01.560 --> 01:08:03.471
I want everyone to know
that I put my heart and soul

01:08:03.600 --> 01:08:06.478
into this music, because Melea
is the love of my life.

01:08:06.600 --> 01:08:08.192
(CHUCKLES) Oh, my God.

01:08:08.280 --> 01:08:09.793
And also that I
will be dancing

01:08:09.880 --> 01:08:11.472
the part of Romeo
to her Juliet

01:08:11.560 --> 01:08:12.959
at the big show
at the Bijou Theater.

01:08:13.480 --> 01:08:15.198
Love of my life.

01:08:15.320 --> 01:08:16.514
Guys, that's amazing, man.

01:08:16.600 --> 01:08:18.555
Can we drop this beat?
Can we, like, hear it guys?

01:08:18.640 --> 01:08:20.631
TAJ: Yo,
ready when you are, man.

01:08:20.720 --> 01:08:21.709
All right, here it is.

01:08:21.800 --> 01:08:24.394
A song by Taj,
produced by Erik Wildwood.

01:08:24.479 --> 01:08:25.707
It's the opening scene

01:08:25.800 --> 01:08:28.439
in Melea Martin's
hip-hop R and J.

01:08:28.520 --> 01:08:29.509
Boo-yah!

01:08:29.600 --> 01:08:31.636
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

01:08:36.279 --> 01:08:37.997
Uncle Simon,
what are you doing?

01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:41.834
It's for my niece's show, man.
With the youngster, Taj.

01:08:41.920 --> 01:08:42.988
Oh, Taj! (LAUGHS)

01:08:47.200 --> 01:08:50.158
Come on, Mama. Let's see those moves.
(SIGHS)

01:08:55.240 --> 01:08:57.231
(LAUGHS)

01:08:57.359 --> 01:08:59.191
You guys are so whack.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:25.988
Whoo!

01:10:04.920 --> 01:10:05.909
(CLICKS)

01:10:06.720 --> 01:10:09.996
You said they were only
using it for rehearsals.

01:10:10.600 --> 01:10:14.070
But there's no rule against the
theater operating, Ms. Lee.

01:10:15.280 --> 01:10:17.748
Don't believe me?
Check the contract.

01:10:17.840 --> 01:10:19.796
I am this close
to killing this deal.

01:10:19.880 --> 01:10:21.029
If you want
this thing to work,

01:10:21.120 --> 01:10:22.758
you had better
start playing ball.

01:10:22.840 --> 01:10:25.115
If you want
this thing to work,

01:10:25.240 --> 01:10:28.357
best you start considering the
community and what they want.

01:10:28.440 --> 01:10:29.429
(LAUGHS)

01:10:31.160 --> 01:10:34.311
They don't want you,
or your theater.

01:10:34.640 --> 01:10:36.437
They've proved that.

01:10:36.760 --> 01:10:38.637
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

01:10:40.560 --> 01:10:41.913
We'll see.

01:11:01.800 --> 01:11:03.438
So, I'm the love
of your life, huh?

01:11:03.760 --> 01:11:05.910
Yeah,
I know, it's pretty corny.

01:11:06.320 --> 01:11:08.515
No, actually,
it's pretty awesome.

01:11:08.600 --> 01:11:09.589
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

01:11:13.240 --> 01:11:15.231
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

01:11:15.600 --> 01:11:16.953
(CLATTERS)
Huh?

01:11:17.040 --> 01:11:19.713
Yeah, yeah, that's it.
That one.

01:11:19.800 --> 01:11:23.236
Now, now, move it a bit to the left.
Yeah. Little more.

01:11:23.320 --> 01:11:24.912
Little... That's it. Good.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:27.639
That's perfect.
Now, this one.

01:11:31.440 --> 01:11:32.793
Hey.
Hey.

01:11:34.400 --> 01:11:36.356
(NADINE GASPS AND EXCLAIMS)

01:11:36.440 --> 01:11:38.556
I can't believe it.
Neither can I.

01:11:38.640 --> 01:11:40.278
Shoot, I can.

01:11:40.760 --> 01:11:42.830
Thank you, guys,
for not giving up on me.

01:11:43.440 --> 01:11:46.750
Looks like we're gonna need
to add another performance.

01:11:48.120 --> 01:11:50.998
So, you get to change
the world after all.

01:11:52.120 --> 01:11:55.715
ISHANI: The world? I'll
settle for that dance space.

01:11:55.800 --> 01:11:57.199
MELEA: Me, too.

01:11:57.520 --> 01:11:59.272
But we still need
to find a new place.

01:11:59.640 --> 01:12:00.629
Wow.

01:12:00.720 --> 01:12:02.870
You really know how to suck
the life out of everything.

01:12:02.960 --> 01:12:03.949
Right?

01:12:04.040 --> 01:12:05.917
I don't know how you've
been her friend for so long.

01:12:06.000 --> 01:12:07.672
Yeah, neither do I.

01:12:08.120 --> 01:12:09.109
(CHUCKLES)

01:12:13.640 --> 01:12:15.756
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:12:18.960 --> 01:12:19.949
Phew.

01:13:12.360 --> 01:13:14.078
Stop, stop, stop.
ISHANI: Why?

01:13:14.440 --> 01:13:16.396
He's great. It's the ending.
I don't like it.

01:13:16.480 --> 01:13:17.799
Melea...

01:13:18.480 --> 01:13:21.392
No, seriously. I mean, we all
end up dead, and that's it?

01:13:21.480 --> 01:13:22.959
Hey, you're preaching
to the choir.

01:13:23.040 --> 01:13:24.837
You killed me off
in Act 3, remember?

01:13:26.240 --> 01:13:27.275
I still don't like it.

01:13:27.360 --> 01:13:28.588
So, change it.

01:13:29.040 --> 01:13:30.519
I can't.
Why not?

01:13:31.280 --> 01:13:32.918
Prokofiev wanted to
change the ending, too,

01:13:33.000 --> 01:13:34.069
but his investors
wouldn't let him.

01:13:34.800 --> 01:13:36.279
So, you're saying
just change the story?

01:13:36.360 --> 01:13:37.349
ERIK: Why not?

01:13:38.120 --> 01:13:39.678
You already changed the dance.

01:13:41.880 --> 01:13:45.509
Yeah, Melea. Haven't we all had
enough tragedy in our lives?

01:13:45.600 --> 01:13:47.113
Let's take back control.

01:13:49.760 --> 01:13:50.795
Yeah.

01:13:51.280 --> 01:13:52.633
You're right.
Yeah.

01:13:53.800 --> 01:13:56.758
Okay, everybody.
It's gonna be a long night.

01:14:01.280 --> 01:14:02.508
Careful with that, man.

01:14:08.520 --> 01:14:11.717
ISHANI'S MOM: 'Shani, come on!
We gotta go!

01:14:11.840 --> 01:14:13.319
Yeah, coming!

01:14:24.480 --> 01:14:25.515
Wish me luck.

01:14:30.000 --> 01:14:31.991
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

01:14:44.520 --> 01:14:45.669
Thank you.
Thank you.

01:14:51.600 --> 01:14:54.034
And this must...
This little one. Okay?

01:14:57.720 --> 01:14:58.709
Phew.

01:15:00.120 --> 01:15:01.872
Don't worry.
It's gonna be fine.

01:15:03.320 --> 01:15:05.914
Right. You do this
all the time, bro.

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:07.877
I feel like I'm gonna
have a heart attack.

01:15:09.000 --> 01:15:11.036
Then before you die,
you should know something.

01:15:12.640 --> 01:15:13.709
What?

01:15:14.400 --> 01:15:15.958
You hit like a girl.
(CHUCKLES)

01:15:17.240 --> 01:15:18.229
Thanks.

01:15:18.320 --> 01:15:20.629
Better?
Better, yes. Thanks.

01:15:20.720 --> 01:15:22.756
All right.
Gotta get to my seat.

01:15:22.840 --> 01:15:24.159
All right. Enjoy.

01:15:25.440 --> 01:15:26.429
Phew.

01:15:27.200 --> 01:15:30.397
Then it's like...
Okay, round...

01:15:30.760 --> 01:15:33.228
So, you ready to get serious?

01:15:33.320 --> 01:15:34.673
ALL: Yeah!

01:15:36.760 --> 01:15:37.749
(ALL GASPING)

01:15:37.840 --> 01:15:38.829
Ow!

01:15:42.200 --> 01:15:43.599
Thank you, Mama.

01:15:44.640 --> 01:15:47.234
Yes, thank you,
Mrs. Mfeke, so much.

01:15:48.240 --> 01:15:51.232
So, any last words
for the troops?

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:53.353
Let's do this.

01:15:53.440 --> 01:15:55.556
(ALL CHEERING)

01:15:59.440 --> 01:16:02.352
FEMALE ANNOUNCER: Ladies and
gentlemen, please take your seats,

01:16:02.440 --> 01:16:04.670
turn off your cell phones,
and enjoy the show.

01:16:04.760 --> 01:16:05.749
Sit down.

01:16:10.960 --> 01:16:13.030
(APPLAUSE)

01:16:15.120 --> 01:16:18.874
For never was a story
of more woe than this,

01:16:18.960 --> 01:16:21.269
of Juliet and her Romeo.

01:16:21.360 --> 01:16:23.999
Two young people from
different sides of the track,

01:16:24.080 --> 01:16:25.479
two lovers star-crossed.

01:16:26.880 --> 01:16:31.032
Now, Romeo, being a Montague,
and Juliet, being a Capulet,

01:16:31.120 --> 01:16:33.475
meant that their love
could never be accurate.

01:16:33.960 --> 01:16:35.359
Their families
were sworn enemies,

01:16:35.440 --> 01:16:37.351
so them being in love
would just add to it.

01:16:38.080 --> 01:16:40.753
The ongoing fights about
who's wrong and right,

01:16:40.840 --> 01:16:43.957
but after all these years, still,
two wrongs don't make a right.

01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:48.353
Sharing a love strong
enough to die and kill for,

01:16:48.440 --> 01:16:50.590
the kind of love that everyone
should try and live for.

01:16:51.120 --> 01:16:54.032
So, please, if you will,
open eyes, all attend,

01:16:54.120 --> 01:16:56.759
the show must begin, but
I'll be back before it ends.

01:16:57.320 --> 01:16:59.356
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:04.991
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:17:34.680 --> 01:17:36.193
They gettin' into it already.

01:17:42.440 --> 01:17:43.475
Whoa!

01:17:46.240 --> 01:17:47.229
(APPLAUSE)

01:18:23.760 --> 01:18:25.079
(APPLAUSE)

01:18:34.880 --> 01:18:35.869
Ooh!

01:18:38.640 --> 01:18:40.198
(ALL CHEERING)

01:18:53.200 --> 01:18:54.189
(CLATTERS)

01:19:28.400 --> 01:19:29.389
Whoo!

01:19:55.800 --> 01:19:57.358
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

01:19:57.480 --> 01:19:59.710
Go, Juliet! Mm!
(LAUGHS)

01:20:21.360 --> 01:20:22.475
Whoo!

01:20:22.560 --> 01:20:24.198
That's what we came to see!

01:20:56.240 --> 01:20:57.229
Oh!

01:20:57.320 --> 01:20:59.356
Yeah, all right!
Whoo!

01:21:14.920 --> 01:21:15.909
(SWORDS CLINK)

01:21:21.800 --> 01:21:22.789
CROWD: Ooh!

01:21:33.440 --> 01:21:34.953
(CROWD GROANS)

01:21:42.600 --> 01:21:44.591
It's just a dance, baby.

01:21:45.520 --> 01:21:48.592
No, Mama. It's so much more.

01:22:28.080 --> 01:22:30.036
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

01:22:36.760 --> 01:22:39.069
Guys, can you believe this?

01:22:39.160 --> 01:22:40.229
It's insane.

01:22:41.160 --> 01:22:42.593
Ishani, you okay, baby?

01:22:42.680 --> 01:22:44.591
You want me to get some
revenge on Romeo over there?

01:22:44.680 --> 01:22:45.908
Nah, it's cool.

01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:48.558
Hey, you okay?

01:22:49.600 --> 01:22:52.876
What's wrong? Nothing at all.
I'm fine.

01:22:53.640 --> 01:22:56.837
Guess I just can't believe that
this is all finally happening.

01:22:57.520 --> 01:22:59.033
I wish my mom
could've seen it.

01:23:02.840 --> 01:23:06.833
Um, you lovebirds need to save
all of this for the stage.

01:23:06.960 --> 01:23:08.712
The intermission is over.

01:23:09.480 --> 01:23:11.038
(CLAPS) Okay, people!

01:23:12.520 --> 01:23:13.839
It's time to rock.

01:23:13.920 --> 01:23:15.069
Yes!
(ALL CHEERING)

01:23:15.160 --> 01:23:16.354
Let's go!

01:23:18.880 --> 01:23:20.950
(CHEERING)

01:23:28.680 --> 01:23:31.513
These violent delights
have violent ends,

01:23:32.160 --> 01:23:34.230
drawing swords,
spilling blood.

01:23:34.360 --> 01:23:36.112
Vicious brawls over grudges.

01:23:36.240 --> 01:23:37.673
Vengeance and
rage lead to death,

01:23:37.760 --> 01:23:39.591
leaving no room
for discussions.

01:23:40.280 --> 01:23:43.078
Banished for his actions,
Romeo has got to leave.

01:23:43.720 --> 01:23:46.837
Will they ever be together? We'll
just have to wait and see.

01:23:46.920 --> 01:23:49.036
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

01:23:50.800 --> 01:23:52.870
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:23:52.960 --> 01:23:53.949
Whoo!

01:24:21.920 --> 01:24:22.909
(WHISTLING)

01:26:07.200 --> 01:26:08.952
(HEART BEATING)

01:26:09.040 --> 01:26:10.632
They want her
to marry that guy.

01:26:11.320 --> 01:26:12.435
It's not good.

01:26:12.560 --> 01:26:14.073
(THUMPING)

01:26:14.160 --> 01:26:16.230
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:26:16.320 --> 01:26:18.470
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:26:59.520 --> 01:27:00.873
Did she really kill herself?

01:27:00.960 --> 01:27:02.234
Nah, she's just faking.

01:27:02.320 --> 01:27:03.673
But then she can't be...
Come on, show respect.

01:27:03.760 --> 01:27:04.749
Okay.

01:27:04.840 --> 01:27:06.478
(INAUDIBLE)

01:27:17.600 --> 01:27:19.158
(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)

01:27:22.240 --> 01:27:23.229
Whoo!

01:27:30.280 --> 01:27:33.033
Things have come full circle
in the state of despair.

01:27:33.680 --> 01:27:36.353
Juliet holds the solution in
her hand and just stares.

01:27:37.480 --> 01:27:39.072
Slowly dancing
with the potion,

01:27:39.160 --> 01:27:40.752
yeah, she's going
through the motions.

01:27:41.080 --> 01:27:44.709
A selfless sacrifice, hoping
the gates of love will open.

01:27:44.800 --> 01:27:47.917
Ready to die for her love,
ready to rise up above.

01:27:48.440 --> 01:27:50.874
Putting an end to all the pain is
all she's hoping that it does.

01:27:53.120 --> 01:27:56.271
So, will Romeo come save his
only love before her time's out?

01:27:57.800 --> 01:27:59.313
Will true love prevail?

01:28:00.200 --> 01:28:01.713
The time has come
for us to find out.

01:28:01.800 --> 01:28:03.995
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

01:28:07.160 --> 01:28:08.149
Whoo-hoo!

01:28:11.880 --> 01:28:13.791
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

01:28:15.840 --> 01:28:17.990
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

01:29:49.040 --> 01:29:51.076
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

01:30:04.600 --> 01:30:06.556
Yeah, that's what
I'm talking about.

01:30:18.440 --> 01:30:20.431
(ALL CHEERING)

01:30:31.240 --> 01:30:35.028
You know, when Nureyev danced this,
they clapped for 40 minutes.

01:30:35.440 --> 01:30:37.476
(SCOFFS) Is that right? Mm-hmm.

01:30:38.840 --> 01:30:41.070
(CHEERING)

01:30:45.320 --> 01:30:47.390
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

01:30:55.800 --> 01:30:56.835
I don't even know what to say.

01:30:57.200 --> 01:30:59.191
Say you did it.
We all did it.

01:31:01.560 --> 01:31:03.437
Well, I imagine you
won't have much trouble

01:31:03.560 --> 01:31:04.834
